CEBUF.summary: Cebu Air, Inc. provides air transportation services. It offers air travel services to passengers, as well as airport-to-airport cargo services on its domestic and international routes. The company also provides ancillary services, such as cancellation and rebooking options; in-flight merchandising, including sale of duty-free products on international flights; baggage services; and travel-related products and services. As of June 30, 2020, it operated a fleet of 77 aircraft, including 30 Airbus A320, 7 Airbus A321 CEO, 5 Airbus A320 NEO, 6 Airbus A321 NEO, 8 Airbus A330 CEO, 8 ATR 72-500, and 13 ATR 72-600. The company was founded in 1988 and is headquartered in Pasay City, the Philippines. Cebu Air, Inc. is a subsidiary of CP Air Holdings, Inc.
